# Normalize all text files to LF in the repository regardless of the
# contributor's platform. Combined with .editorconfig (end_of_line = lf),
# this eliminates the "LF will be replaced by CRLF" warnings on Windows
# checkouts and prevents diffs that are "really" just line-ending churn.
#
# `text=auto`  → git auto-detects text vs binary
# `eol=lf`     → text files use LF in the working tree (Linux/Mac/CI),
#                even on Windows
* text=auto eol=lf

# Lock binary file types — git must never apply line-ending normalization
# to these or they'd corrupt.
*.png  binary
*.jpg  binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif  binary
*.ico  binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
*.pdf  binary
*.db   binary
*.sqlite binary
